    "## 1. Introduction\n",
    "\n",
    "This project presents a structured comparative analysis of three supervised machine learning models using one of the datasets provided for this course.\n",
    "\n",
    "Among the available candidate datasets, the Hotel Reservations Dataset was selected due to its clearly defined binary classification task, heterogeneous feature space, and realistic behavioral characteristics. These properties make it well-suited for evaluating differences in model performance, robustness, and interpretability across algorithmic families.\n",
    "\n",
    "The prediction objective is to determine whether a reservation will be canceled or not. While the dataset originates from a hospitality context, the primary focus of this project is methodological rather than domain-specific. The goal is to systematically analyze preprocessing strategies, model selection decisions, and evaluation metrics under realistic data conditions.\n",
    "\n",
    "The workflow includes dataset justification, exploratory data analysis, preprocessing design, model training, hyperparameter tuning, comparative evaluation, and an assessment of ethical and fairness considerations. This structured approach ensures both technical rigor and responsible machine learning practice."
   ]
  },
