   "source": [
    "### 6.1 Preprocessing goals and guiding principles\n",
    "\n",
    "The preprocessing strategy in this project is designed to ensure stable model training and fair comparison between algorithms. Since the goal is to compare supervised learning methods rather than preprocessing techniques, the same preprocessing pipeline is applied consistently across all models. This ensures that performance differences are due to model behavior and not differences in data preparation. At the same time, unnecessary information loss is avoided in order to preserve the original data distribution as much as possible.\n",
    "\n",
    "The preprocessing workflow includes identifier removal, duplicate inspection, missing value checks, outlier mitigation based on quantiles, categorical encoding, and numerical scaling using a unified ColumnTransformer. All transformations are fitted exclusively on the training data and then applied unchanged to the test set to prevent data leakage.\n",
    "\n",
    "As part of these initial steps, the variable Booking_ID is removed from both training and test sets, since it represents a unique identifier without predictive value. In addition, duplicate rows are detected and removed from the training set while keeping the first occurrence. The test set remains unchanged to preserve an unbiased evaluation. After removing duplicates, the target variable is realigned with the filtered training data to maintain correct label correspondence, and the resulting dataset dimensions are documented."
