    "The preprocessing pipeline is implemented using `Pipeline` and `ColumnTransformer` to ensure a structured and leakage-free transformation process.\n",
    "\n",
    "For numerical features, a two-step pipeline is defined. First, missing values are imputed using the median. Although no missing values were detected in the current dataset, this step ensures robustness in case future data versions contain missing entries. Second, `RobustScaler` is applied to scale numerical variables based on the median and interquartile range, which reduces sensitivity to extreme values.\n",
    "\n",
    "For categorical features, a separate pipeline is constructed. Missing values are imputed using the most frequent category, and one-hot encoding is applied to convert categorical levels into binary indicator variables. The parameter `handle_unknown=\"ignore\"` ensures that unseen categories in the test set do not cause errors during transformation.\n",
    "\n",
    "Both pipelines are combined within a single `ColumnTransformer`, which applies the appropriate transformation to each feature group. The transformer is fitted exclusively on the training data using `fit_transform(X_train)` and then applied unchanged to the test data using `transform(X_test)`. This design prevents data leakage and ensures a fair evaluation.\n",
