    "\n",
    "The results of this project raise several ethical considerations that extend beyond purely technical model selection. As identified during exploratory analysis, variables such as market_segment_type and repeated_guest exhibit strong predictive power. However, these features may also function as indirect proxies for demographic, socioeconomic, or behavioral characteristics. A model that relies heavily on market segment, for example, could systematically assign higher cancellation risk to customers booking through online channels. In operational contexts, such predictions might translate into stricter cancellation conditions, higher required deposits, or differential treatment across booking channels. Given that online bookings account for a substantial proportion of reservations, even small systematic biases could affect a large number of customers.\n",
